Note:
This file handles code completion and LSP completion integration.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process code completion and LSP completion integration
- Handle completion suggestions and completion ranking
- Manage completion context and completion filtering
- Process completion communication and completion protocol implementation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Code completion enables LSP completion integration and completion support
- Proper completion handling ensures correct completion suggestion generation
- Completion support enables Runa compilation for LSP-integrated completion handling

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Keyword completion for all Runa language keywords
- Identifier completion from current scope and imported modules
- Member access completion for struct field and method access
- Annotation completion for the @Reasoning, @Implementation annotation system
- CompletionItem construction with kind, detail, and sort text

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa for safe memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa for heap allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for list management
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa" as MemorySafety
Import "compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa" as OwnedUtils
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Completion Data Structures
Note: ============================================================================

Note: CompletionItem structure (40 bytes total, 5 fields x 8 bytes each)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  label (8 bytes) - Pointer to display text for the completion
Note:   offset 8:  kind (8 bytes) - CompletionItemKind constant value
Note:   offset 16: detail (8 bytes) - Pointer to optional detail/type info string
Note:   offset 24: insert_text (8 bytes) - Pointer to text to insert when completing
Note:   offset 32: sort_text (8 bytes) - Pointer to text used for sorting order

Type called "CompletionItem":
    label as Integer
    kind as Integer
    detail as Integer
    insert_text as Integer
    sort_text as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CompletionItemKind Constants (LSP specification values)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant COMPLETION_KIND_KEYWORD as Integer is 1
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_FUNCTION as Integer is 2
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_VARIABLE as Integer is 3
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_TYPE as Integer is 4
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_MODULE as Integer is 5
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_ANNOTATION as Integer is 6
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_FIELD as Integer is 7
Constant COMPLETION_KIND_CONSTANT as Integer is 8

Note: Maximum number of completion items to return per request
Constant MAX_COMPLETION_ITEMS as Integer is 256

Note: Completion trigger context
Constant TRIGGER_INVOKED as Integer is 1
Constant TRIGGER_CHARACTER as Integer is 2
Constant TRIGGER_INCOMPLETE as Integer is 3

Note: Return codes
Constant COMPLETION_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant COMPLETION_FAILED as Integer is -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Runa Keyword Definitions
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Total number of Runa keywords available for completion
Constant RUNA_KEYWORD_COUNT as Integer is 38

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Core Completion Logic
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_completions" takes document_text as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer, trigger_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate a list of completion items for the given cursor position
    Note: Analyzes the document text around the cursor to determine context:
    Note:   - If cursor follows a dot: member access completion
    Note:   - If cursor follows '@': annotation completion
    Note:   - If cursor is at start of line or after whitespace: keyword + identifier completion
    Note:   - Otherwise: identifier completion filtered by prefix
    Note:
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   document_text - Pointer to full document text string
    Note:   cursor_line - Zero-based line number of cursor
    Note:   cursor_col - Zero-based column of cursor
    Note:   trigger_kind - TRIGGER_INVOKED, TRIGGER_CHARACTER, or TRIGGER_INCOMPLETE
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to completion list structure (ArrayList of CompletionItem pointers)
    Note: Returns 0 on failure

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate the completion results list
    Note: ArrayList structure: data ptr (8), size (8), capacity (8), element_size (8) = 32 bytes
    Let result_list be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 32
    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Initialize result list with capacity for MAX_COMPLETION_ITEMS pointers
    Let items_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_COMPLETION_ITEMS multiplied by 8
    If items_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result_list
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 0, items_array
    Let dummy_size be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8, 0
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 16, MAX_COMPLETION_ITEMS
    Let dummy_elem be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 24, 8

    Note: Find the character immediately before the cursor to determine context
    Let trigger_char be proc get_char_at_position from document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col - 1
    Let prefix_ptr be proc extract_word_prefix from document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col

    Note: Determine completion context based on trigger character
    Note: Dot (46) = member access, @ (64) = annotation, otherwise = keywords + identifiers

    If trigger_char is equal to 46:
        Note: Member access completion (e.g., "obj." triggers field/method completion)
        Let member_result be proc complete_member_access with document_text, cursor_line, cursor_col, result_list
    Otherwise If trigger_char is equal to 64:
        Note: Annotation completion (e.g., "@" triggers annotation name completion)
        Let annotation_result be proc complete_annotations with result_list
    Otherwise:
        Note: General completion - keywords and identifiers filtered by prefix
        Let keyword_result be proc complete_keywords with prefix_ptr, result_list
        Let ident_result be proc complete_identifiers with document_text, prefix_ptr, cursor_line, result_list
    End If

    Note: Free prefix string if allocated
    If prefix_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_prefix be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with prefix_ptr
    End If

    Return result_list
End Process

Process called "complete_keywords" takes prefix as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add matching Runa language keywords to the completion list
    Note: Filters keywords by the given prefix (case-insensitive first character match)
    Note: Adds each matching keyword as a CompletionItem with COMPLETION_KIND_KEYWORD
    Note:
    Note: Runa keywords include all control flow, declarations, and built-in constructs:
    Note:   Let, Set, If, Otherwise, While, For, Each, End, Return, Process, Type,
    Note:   Constant, Import, Match, When, Break, Continue, Note, Private, Try, Catch,
    Note:   Finally, Throw, Loop, Yield, Async, Await, Spawn, Send, Receive,
    Note:   Protocol, Static, Unless, From, As, and, or, not, is, be, takes, returns, called, that
    Note:
    Note: Returns number of keyword items added

    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items_added be 0

    Note: Define all Runa keywords with their display text
    Note: Each keyword is stored as a small allocation containing the keyword bytes

    Note: Control flow keywords
    Let kw_let be proc create_keyword_string from 76, 101, 116, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_set be proc create_keyword_string from 83, 101, 116, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_if be proc create_keyword_string from 73, 102, 0, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_otherwise be proc create_keyword_string from 79, 116, 104, 101, 114, 119
    Let kw_while be proc create_keyword_string from 87, 104, 105, 108, 101, 0
    Let kw_for be proc create_keyword_string from 70, 111, 114, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_each be proc create_keyword_string from 69, 97, 99, 104, 0, 0
    Let kw_end be proc create_keyword_string from 69, 110, 100, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_return be proc create_keyword_string from 82, 101, 116, 117, 114, 110
    Let kw_process be proc create_keyword_string from 80, 114, 111, 99, 101, 115
    Let kw_type be proc create_keyword_string from 84, 121, 112, 101, 0, 0
    Let kw_constant be proc create_keyword_string from 67, 111, 110, 115, 116, 97
    Let kw_import be proc create_keyword_string from 73, 109, 112, 111, 114, 116
    Let kw_match be proc create_keyword_string from 77, 97, 116, 99, 104, 0
    Let kw_when be proc create_keyword_string from 87, 104, 101, 110, 0, 0
    Let kw_break be proc create_keyword_string from 66, 114, 101, 97, 107, 0
    Let kw_continue be proc create_keyword_string from 67, 111, 110, 116, 105, 110
    Let kw_note be proc create_keyword_string from 78, 111, 116, 101, 0, 0
    Let kw_private be proc create_keyword_string from 80, 114, 105, 118, 97, 116
    Let kw_try be proc create_keyword_string from 84, 114, 121, 0, 0, 0
    Let kw_catch be proc create_keyword_string from 67, 97, 116, 99, 104, 0
    Let kw_finally be proc create_keyword_string from 70, 105, 110, 97, 108, 108
    Let kw_throw be proc create_keyword_string from 84, 104, 114, 111, 119, 0
    Let kw_loop be proc create_keyword_string from 76, 111, 111, 112, 0, 0
    Let kw_yield be proc create_keyword_string from 89, 105, 101, 108, 100, 0

    Note: Build an array of all keyword pointers for iteration
    Let kw_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 200
    If kw_array is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_k0 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 0, kw_let
    Let dummy_k1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 8, kw_set
    Let dummy_k2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 16, kw_if
    Let dummy_k3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 24, kw_otherwise
    Let dummy_k4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 32, kw_while
    Let dummy_k5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 40, kw_for
    Let dummy_k6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 48, kw_each
    Let dummy_k7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 56, kw_end
    Let dummy_k8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 64, kw_return
    Let dummy_k9 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 72, kw_process
    Let dummy_k10 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 80, kw_type
    Let dummy_k11 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 88, kw_constant
    Let dummy_k12 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 96, kw_import
    Let dummy_k13 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 104, kw_match
    Let dummy_k14 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 112, kw_when
    Let dummy_k15 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 120, kw_break
    Let dummy_k16 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 128, kw_continue
    Let dummy_k17 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 136, kw_note
    Let dummy_k18 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 144, kw_private
    Let dummy_k19 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 152, kw_try
    Let dummy_k20 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 160, kw_catch
    Let dummy_k21 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 168, kw_finally
    Let dummy_k22 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 176, kw_throw
    Let dummy_k23 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 184, kw_loop
    Let dummy_k24 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, 192, kw_yield

    Let keyword_count be 25

    Note: Iterate through keywords and add matching ones to the result list
    Let kw_idx be 0
    While kw_idx < keyword_count:
        Let kw_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with kw_array, kw_idx multiplied by 8
        If kw_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_matches_prefix from kw_ptr, prefix
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Note: Create a CompletionItem for this keyword
                Let item be proc create_completion_item with kw_ptr, COMPLETION_KIND_KEYWORD, 0, kw_ptr, 0
                If item is not equal to 0:
                    Note: Add to result list
                    Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8
                    Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 16
                    If current_size < capacity:
                        Let items_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 0
                        Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with items_data, current_size multiplied by 8, item
                        Let dummy_inc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8, current_size + 1
                        Set items_added to items_added + 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set kw_idx to kw_idx + 1
    End While

    Let dummy_free_arr be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with kw_array
    Return items_added
End Process

Process called "complete_identifiers" takes document_text as Integer, prefix as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add identifier completions from the document scope
    Note: Scans the document for Let/Set/Process/Type/Constant declarations
    Note: and adds matching identifiers to the completion list
    Note:
    Note: Strategy:
    Note: 1. Scan document text for declaration keywords (Let, Set, Process, Type, Constant)
    Note: 2. Extract the identifier name following each declaration keyword
    Note: 3. Filter by prefix match
    Note: 4. Assign appropriate CompletionItemKind based on declaration type
    Note: 5. Deduplicate by tracking seen identifiers
    Note:
    Note: Returns number of identifier items added

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items_added be 0

    Note: Scan through document text looking for declaration patterns
    Note: We look for "Let ", "Set ", "Process ", "Type ", "Constant " at line starts
    Let scan_pos be 0
    Let doc_len be proc measure_null_terminated_length from document_text

    Note: Track seen identifiers to avoid duplicates (simple array of up to 128 pointers)
    Let seen_idents be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 1024
    If seen_idents is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let seen_count be 0
    Let max_seen be 128

    While scan_pos < doc_len:
        Note: Check for "Let " at current position (L=76, e=101, t=116, space=32)
        Let ch0 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos
        Let ident_kind be 0
        Let ident_start be 0

        If ch0 is equal to 76:
            Note: Potential "Let " declaration
            If scan_pos + 3 < doc_len:
                Let ch1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 1
                Let ch2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 2
                Let ch3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 3
                If ch1 is equal to 101:
                    If ch2 is equal to 116:
                        If ch3 is equal to 32:
                            Set ident_kind to COMPLETION_KIND_VARIABLE
                            Set ident_start to scan_pos + 4
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If ch0 is equal to 80:
            Note: Potential "Process " declaration (P=80, r=114, o=111, c=99, e=101, s=115, s=115, space=32)
            If scan_pos + 7 < doc_len:
                Set ch1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 1
                Let ch6 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 6
                Let ch7 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 7
                If ch1 is equal to 114:
                    If ch6 is equal to 115:
                        If ch7 is equal to 32:
                            Set ident_kind to COMPLETION_KIND_FUNCTION
                            Note: Skip "Process called " to get to the name
                            Note: "Process called " = 16 characters, then quote, then name
                            Set ident_start to scan_pos + 17
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If ch0 is equal to 84:
            Note: Potential "Type " declaration (T=84, y=121, p=112, e=101, space=32)
            If scan_pos + 4 < doc_len:
                Set ch1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 1
                Let ch4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 4
                If ch1 is equal to 121:
                    If ch4 is equal to 32:
                        Set ident_kind to COMPLETION_KIND_TYPE
                        Note: Skip "Type called " = 13 chars, then quote
                        Set ident_start to scan_pos + 14
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If ch0 is equal to 67:
            Note: Potential "Constant " declaration (C=67, o=111, n=110, s=115, t=116, a=97, n=110, t=116, space=32)
            If scan_pos + 8 < doc_len:
                Set ch1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 1
                Let ch8 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan_pos + 8
                If ch1 is equal to 111:
                    If ch8 is equal to 32:
                        Set ident_kind to COMPLETION_KIND_CONSTANT
                        Set ident_start to scan_pos + 9
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: If we found a declaration, extract the identifier name
        If ident_kind is not equal to 0:
            If ident_start > 0:
                If ident_start < doc_len:
                    Note: Extract identifier name (alphanumeric + underscore until space/newline/quote)
                    Let ident_end be ident_start
                    While ident_end < doc_len:
                        Let ic be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ident_end
                        Note: Stop at space (32), newline (10), carriage return (13), quote (34), colon (58)
                        If ic is equal to 32:
                            Set ident_end to doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic is equal to 10:
                            Set ident_end to doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic is equal to 13:
                            Set ident_end to doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic is equal to 34:
                            Set ident_end to doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic is equal to 58:
                            Set ident_end to doc_len
                        Otherwise:
                            Set ident_end to ident_end + 1
                        End If
                    End While

                    Note: Calculate actual end position (ident_end was pushed to doc_len as sentinel)
                    Let actual_end be ident_end
                    If actual_end > doc_len:
                        Set actual_end to doc_len
                    End If
                    Note: Recalculate by re-scanning from ident_start
                    Set actual_end to ident_start
                    While actual_end < doc_len:
                        Let ic2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, actual_end
                        If ic2 is equal to 32:
                            Set actual_end to actual_end + doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic2 is equal to 10:
                            Set actual_end to actual_end + doc_len
                        Otherwise If ic2 is equal to 34:
                            Set actual_end to actual_end + doc_len
                        Otherwise:
                            Set actual_end to actual_end + 1
                        End If
                    End While
                    Note: Adjust for the sentinel jump
                    If actual_end > doc_len:
                        Set actual_end to actual_end - doc_len
                    End If

                    Let ident_len be actual_end - ident_start
                    If ident_len > 0:
                        If ident_len < 256:
                            Note: Copy the identifier name
                            Let ident_copy be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with ident_len + 1
                            If ident_copy is not equal to 0:
                                Let cp_idx be 0
                                While cp_idx < ident_len:
                                    Let ib be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ident_start + cp_idx
                                    Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ident_copy, cp_idx, ib
                                    Set cp_idx to cp_idx + 1
                                End While
                                Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ident_copy, ident_len, 0

                                Note: Check prefix match
                                Let matches be proc string_matches_prefix from ident_copy, prefix
                                If matches is equal to 1:
                                    Note: Check for duplicates
                                    Let is_dup be proc check_duplicate_ident from seen_idents, seen_count, ident_copy, ident_len
                                    If is_dup is equal to 0:
                                        Note: Add to completion list
                                        Let item be proc create_completion_item with ident_copy, ident_kind, 0, ident_copy, 0
                                        If item is not equal to 0:
                                            Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8
                                            Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 16
                                            If current_size < capacity:
                                                Let items_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 0
                                                Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with items_data, current_size multiplied by 8, item
                                                Let dummy_inc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8, current_size + 1
                                                Set items_added to items_added + 1
                                            End If
                                        End If

                                        Note: Record as seen
                                        If seen_count < max_seen:
                                            Let dummy_seen be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with seen_idents, seen_count multiplied by 8, ident_copy
                                            Set seen_count to seen_count + 1
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Note: Advance to next line
        Let next_nl be scan_pos
        While next_nl < doc_len:
            Let nlc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, next_nl
            If nlc is equal to 10:
                Set scan_pos to next_nl + 1
                Set next_nl to doc_len
            Otherwise:
                Set next_nl to next_nl + 1
            End If
        End While
        If next_nl is equal to doc_len:
            Set scan_pos to doc_len
        End If
    End While

    Let dummy_free_seen be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with seen_idents
    Return items_added
End Process

Process called "complete_member_access" takes document_text as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Provide completions for member access (dot notation)
    Note: When the user types "obj.", we need to determine the type of "obj"
    Note: and provide its fields and methods as completions
    Note:
    Note: Strategy:
    Note: 1. Extract the object identifier before the dot
    Note: 2. Search the document for the type declaration of that identifier
    Note: 3. Find the Type definition and extract its fields
    Note: 4. Add each field as a CompletionItem with COMPLETION_KIND_FIELD
    Note:
    Note: Returns number of member completion items added

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items_added be 0

    Note: Find the identifier before the dot on the current line
    Note: Navigate to cursor_line in the document
    Let line_start be proc find_line_offset from document_text, cursor_line
    If line_start is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan backwards from cursor_col - 1 (skip the dot) to find identifier start
    Let ident_end be cursor_col - 1
    Let ident_scan be ident_end - 1

    While ident_scan > -1:
        Let sc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start + ident_scan
        Note: Identifier chars: a-z (97-122), A-Z (65-90), 0-9 (48-57), _ (95)
        Let is_ident_char be 0
        If sc > 96:
            If sc < 123:
                Set is_ident_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If sc > 64:
            If sc < 91:
                Set is_ident_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If sc > 47:
            If sc < 58:
                Set is_ident_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If sc is equal to 95:
            Set is_ident_char to 1
        End If

        If is_ident_char is equal to 0:
            Set ident_scan to -1
        Otherwise:
            Set ident_scan to ident_scan - 1
        End If
    End While

    Let obj_name_start be ident_scan + 1
    Let obj_name_len be ident_end - obj_name_start

    If obj_name_len < 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy the object name
    Let obj_name be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with obj_name_len + 1
    If obj_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ci be 0
    While ci < obj_name_len:
        Let ob be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_start + obj_name_start + ci
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with obj_name, ci, ob
        Set ci to ci + 1
    End While
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with obj_name, obj_name_len, 0

    Note: Search for the type of this object by finding its declaration
    Note: Look for "Let <obj_name> be a value of type <TypeName>"
    Note: or "Let <obj_name> be of type <TypeName>"
    Let type_name be proc find_variable_type from document_text, obj_name, obj_name_len
    If type_name is not equal to 0:
        Note: Find the Type definition and extract fields
        Let field_count be proc extract_type_fields from document_text, type_name, result_list
        Set items_added to field_count
        Let dummy_free_type be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with type_name
    End If

    Let dummy_free_name be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with obj_name
    Return items_added
End Process

Process called "complete_annotations" takes result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Add Runa annotation completions to the result list
    Note: Provides all standard annotation types from the Runa annotation system:
    Note:   @Reasoning, @Implementation, @Performance_Hints, @Security_Scope,
    Note:   @TestCases, @End, @Deprecated, @External, @Inline, @Pure
    Note: Returns number of annotation items added

    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items_added be 0

    Note: Define annotation names
    Note: @Reasoning (R=82, e=101, a=97, s=115, o=111, n=110)
    Let ann_reasoning be proc create_keyword_string from 82, 101, 97, 115, 111, 110
    Note: @Implementation (I=73, m=109, p=112, l=108, e=101, m=109)
    Let ann_implementation be proc create_keyword_string from 73, 109, 112, 108, 101, 109
    Note: @Performance_Hints (P=80, e=101, r=114, f=102, o=111, r=114)
    Let ann_performance be proc create_keyword_string from 80, 101, 114, 102, 111, 114
    Note: @Security_Scope (S=83, e=101, c=99, u=117, r=114, i=105)
    Let ann_security be proc create_keyword_string from 83, 101, 99, 117, 114, 105
    Note: @TestCases (T=84, e=101, s=115, t=116, C=67, a=97)
    Let ann_testcases be proc create_keyword_string from 84, 101, 115, 116, 67, 97
    Note: @End (E=69, n=110, d=100)
    Let ann_end be proc create_keyword_string from 69, 110, 100, 0, 0, 0
    Note: @Deprecated (D=68, e=101, p=112, r=114, e=101, c=99)
    Let ann_deprecated be proc create_keyword_string from 68, 101, 112, 114, 101, 99
    Note: @External (E=69, x=120, t=116, e=101, r=114, n=110)
    Let ann_external be proc create_keyword_string from 69, 120, 116, 101, 114, 110
    Note: @Inline (I=73, n=110, l=108, i=105, n=110, e=101)
    Let ann_inline be proc create_keyword_string from 73, 110, 108, 105, 110, 101
    Note: @Pure (P=80, u=117, r=114, e=101)
    Let ann_pure be proc create_keyword_string from 80, 117, 114, 101, 0, 0

    Note: Add each annotation to the result list
    Let ann_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 80
    If ann_array is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dummy_a0 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 0, ann_reasoning
    Let dummy_a1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 8, ann_implementation
    Let dummy_a2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 16, ann_performance
    Let dummy_a3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 24, ann_security
    Let dummy_a4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 32, ann_testcases
    Let dummy_a5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 40, ann_end
    Let dummy_a6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 48, ann_deprecated
    Let dummy_a7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 56, ann_external
    Let dummy_a8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 64, ann_inline
    Let dummy_a9 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, 72, ann_pure

    Let ann_count be 10
    Let ann_idx be 0
    While ann_idx < ann_count:
        Let ann_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ann_array, ann_idx multiplied by 8
        If ann_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let item be proc create_completion_item with ann_ptr, COMPLETION_KIND_ANNOTATION, 0, ann_ptr, 0
            If item is not equal to 0:
                Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8
                Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 16
                If current_size < capacity:
                    Let items_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 0
                    Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with items_data, current_size multiplied by 8, item
                    Let dummy_inc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8, current_size + 1
                    Set items_added to items_added + 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set ann_idx to ann_idx + 1
    End While

    Let dummy_free_arr be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with ann_array
    Return items_added
End Process

Process called "create_completion_item" takes label as Integer, kind as Integer, detail as Integer, insert_text as Integer, sort_text as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a new CompletionItem structure with the given properties
    Note: Allocates CompletionItem (40 bytes = 5 fields x 8 bytes)
    Note: If sort_text is 0, uses the label as sort text (alphabetical ordering)
    Note: Returns pointer to CompletionItem, or 0 on allocation failure

    Let item be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 40
    If item is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dummy_label be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 0, label
    Let dummy_kind be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 8, kind
    Let dummy_detail be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 16, detail

    Note: Set insert text (defaults to label if not provided)
    If insert_text is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_insert be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 24, insert_text
    Otherwise:
        Set dummy_insert to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 24, label
    End If

    Note: Set sort text (defaults to label if not provided)
    If sort_text is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_sort be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 32, sort_text
    Otherwise:
        Set dummy_sort to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with item, 32, label
    End If

    Return item
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Processes
Note: ============================================================================

Private Process called "create_keyword_string" takes c1 as Integer, c2 as Integer, c3 as Integer, c4 as Integer, c5 as Integer, c6 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a small string from up to 6 ASCII characters
    Note: Stops at the first 0 byte (used as end marker)
    Note: Returns pointer to null-terminated string, or 0 on failure

    Let str_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 8
    If str_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pos be 0
    If c1 is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c1
        Set pos to pos + 1
    End If
    If c2 is not equal to 0:
        If pos > 0:
            Let dummy2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c2
            Set pos to pos + 1
        End If
    End If
    If c3 is not equal to 0:
        If pos > 0:
            Let dummy3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c3
            Set pos to pos + 1
        End If
    End If
    If c4 is not equal to 0:
        If pos > 0:
            Let dummy4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c4
            Set pos to pos + 1
        End If
    End If
    If c5 is not equal to 0:
        If pos > 0:
            Let dummy5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c5
            Set pos to pos + 1
        End If
    End If
    If c6 is not equal to 0:
        If pos > 0:
            Let dummy6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, c6
            Set pos to pos + 1
        End If
    End If

    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with str_buf, pos, 0
    Return str_buf
End Process

Private Process called "string_matches_prefix" takes str_ptr as Integer, prefix as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if str_ptr starts with the given prefix string
    Note: If prefix is 0 or empty, all strings match
    Note: Returns 1 if match, 0 if no match

    If prefix is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check first byte of prefix - if null, everything matches
    Let first_prefix_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with prefix, 0
    If first_prefix_byte is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If str_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compare prefix bytes against string bytes
    Let idx be 0
    Let max_compare be 256
    While idx < max_compare:
        Let prefix_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with prefix, idx
        If prefix_byte is equal to 0:
            Note: End of prefix reached - all prefix bytes matched
            Return 1
        End If
        Let str_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_ptr, idx
        If str_byte is equal to 0:
            Note: String shorter than prefix
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Case-insensitive comparison: convert both to lowercase
        Let lower_prefix be prefix_byte
        Let lower_str be str_byte
        If lower_prefix > 64:
            If lower_prefix < 91:
                Set lower_prefix to lower_prefix + 32
            End If
        End If
        If lower_str > 64:
            If lower_str < 91:
                Set lower_str to lower_str + 32
            End If
        End If

        If lower_prefix is not equal to lower_str:
            Return 0
        End If

        Set idx to idx + 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Private Process called "get_char_at_position" takes document_text as Integer, line as Integer, col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the character at the given line and column in the document
    Note: Returns the ASCII byte value, or 0 if position is out of bounds

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let line_offset be proc find_line_offset from document_text, line
    If line_offset is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    If col < 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let char_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset + col
    Return char_val
End Process

Private Process called "extract_word_prefix" takes document_text as Integer, cursor_line as Integer, cursor_col as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract the word prefix at the cursor position (text before cursor on same word)
    Note: Scans backwards from cursor to find start of current word
    Note: Returns newly allocated null-terminated string, or 0 if no prefix

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let line_offset be proc find_line_offset from document_text, cursor_line
    If line_offset is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan backwards from cursor_col to find word start
    Let word_end be cursor_col
    Let word_start be cursor_col - 1

    While word_start > -1:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset + word_start
        Note: Check if character is alphanumeric or underscore
        Let is_word_char be 0
        If ch > 96:
            If ch < 123:
                Set is_word_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If ch > 64:
            If ch < 91:
                Set is_word_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If ch > 47:
            If ch < 58:
                Set is_word_char to 1
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 95:
            Set is_word_char to 1
        End If

        If is_word_char is equal to 0:
            Set word_start to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set word_start to word_start - 1
        End If
    End While

    Set word_start to word_start + 1
    Let prefix_len be word_end - word_start

    If prefix_len < 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy the prefix string
    Let prefix_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with prefix_len + 1
    If prefix_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx < prefix_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, line_offset + word_start + idx
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with prefix_buf, idx, byte_val
        Set idx to idx + 1
    End While
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with prefix_buf, prefix_len, 0

    Return prefix_buf
End Process

Private Process called "find_line_offset" takes document_text as Integer, target_line as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find the byte offset where the given line number starts in the document
    Note: Line numbers are zero-based
    Note: Returns byte offset, or -1 if line not found

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    If target_line is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let current_line be 0
    Let offset be 0
    Let max_offset be 1048576

    While offset < max_offset:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, offset
        If ch is equal to 0:
            Return -1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set current_line to current_line + 1
            If current_line is equal to target_line:
                Return offset + 1
            End If
        End If
        Set offset to offset + 1
    End While

    Return -1
End Process

Private Process called "measure_null_terminated_length" takes str_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Measure length of null-terminated string
    Note: Returns byte count before null terminator

    If str_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let len be 0
    Let max_len be 1048576
    While len < max_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_ptr, len
        If byte_val is equal to 0:
            Return len
        End If
        Set len to len + 1
    End While
    Return len
End Process

Private Process called "check_duplicate_ident" takes seen_array as Integer, seen_count as Integer, ident_ptr as Integer, ident_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if an identifier has already been seen
    Note: Compares first bytes of ident_ptr against all entries in seen_array
    Note: Returns 1 if duplicate found, 0 if unique

    If seen_array is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ident_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx < seen_count:
        Let seen_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with seen_array, idx multiplied by 8
        If seen_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Note: Compare first 4 bytes for quick check
            Let match be 1
            Let cmp_idx be 0
            While cmp_idx < ident_len:
                Let seen_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with seen_ptr, cmp_idx
                Let ident_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with ident_ptr, cmp_idx
                If seen_byte is not equal to ident_byte:
                    Set match to 0
                    Set cmp_idx to ident_len
                End If
                Set cmp_idx to cmp_idx + 1
            End While
            Note: Also check that seen string terminates at the same position
            If match is equal to 1:
                Let seen_term be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with seen_ptr, ident_len
                If seen_term is equal to 0:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx + 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "find_variable_type" takes document_text as Integer, var_name as Integer, var_name_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find the type of a variable by searching for its declaration in the document
    Note: Looks for patterns like "Let <var_name> be a value of type <TypeName>"
    Note: or "takes <var_name> as <TypeName>"
    Note: Returns pointer to newly allocated type name string, or 0 if not found

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If var_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan the document for the variable name followed by type information
    Let doc_len be proc measure_null_terminated_length from document_text
    Let scan be 0

    While scan < doc_len:
        Note: Look for "type " keyword which follows the variable name in declarations
        Note: t=116, y=121, p=112, e=101, space=32
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan
        If ch is equal to 116:
            If scan + 4 < doc_len:
                Let ch1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan + 1
                Let ch2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan + 2
                Let ch3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan + 3
                Let ch4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan + 4
                If ch1 is equal to 121:
                    If ch2 is equal to 112:
                        If ch3 is equal to 101:
                            If ch4 is equal to 32:
                                Note: Found "type " - extract the type name that follows
                                Let type_start be scan + 5
                                Let type_end be type_start
                                While type_end < doc_len:
                                    Let tc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, type_end
                                    If tc is equal to 32:
                                        Set type_end to type_end + doc_len
                                    Otherwise If tc is equal to 10:
                                        Set type_end to type_end + doc_len
                                    Otherwise If tc is equal to 13:
                                        Set type_end to type_end + doc_len
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Set type_end to type_end + 1
                                    End If
                                End While
                                If type_end > doc_len:
                                    Set type_end to type_end - doc_len
                                End If

                                Let type_len be type_end - type_start
                                If type_len > 0:
                                    If type_len < 256:
                                        Let type_copy be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with type_len + 1
                                        If type_copy is not equal to 0:
                                            Let ci be 0
                                            While ci < type_len:
                                                Let tb be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, type_start + ci
                                                Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with type_copy, ci, tb
                                                Set ci to ci + 1
                                            End While
                                            Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with type_copy, type_len, 0
                                            Return type_copy
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set scan to scan + 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "extract_type_fields" takes document_text as Integer, type_name as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract fields from a Type definition and add them as completion items
    Note: Searches for "Type called "<type_name>":" and extracts field declarations
    Note: Returns number of field completion items added

    If document_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let fields_added be 0
    Let doc_len be proc measure_null_terminated_length from document_text
    Let type_name_len be proc measure_null_terminated_length from type_name

    Note: Search for "Type called " followed by the type name
    Note: T=84, y=121, p=112, e=101
    Let scan be 0
    Let type_body_start be -1

    While scan < doc_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan
        If ch is equal to 84:
            Note: Check for "Type called "
            If scan + 13 < doc_len:
                Let ch1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, scan + 1
                If ch1 is equal to 121:
                    Note: Skip to after "Type called \"" and check for type name match
                    Let name_check_start be scan + 14
                    Let name_matches be 1
                    Let ni be 0
                    While ni < type_name_len:
                        If name_check_start + ni < doc_len:
                            Let name_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, name_check_start + ni
                            Let type_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with type_name, ni
                            If name_ch is not equal to type_ch:
                                Set name_matches to 0
                                Set ni to type_name_len
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set ni to ni + 1
                    End While

                    If name_matches is equal to 1:
                        Note: Found the type definition - find the body start (after the colon on the next line)
                        Let body_scan be name_check_start + type_name_len
                        While body_scan < doc_len:
                            Let bc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, body_scan
                            If bc is equal to 10:
                                Set type_body_start to body_scan + 1
                                Set body_scan to doc_len
                            End If
                            Set body_scan to body_scan + 1
                        End While
                        Set scan to doc_len
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set scan to scan + 1
    End While

    If type_body_start is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse field declarations from the type body
    Note: Each field line looks like: "    field_name as DataType"
    Note: Stop at "End Type"
    Let field_scan be type_body_start
    While field_scan < doc_len:
        Note: Skip leading whitespace
        Let ws_skip be field_scan
        While ws_skip < doc_len:
            Let wc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ws_skip
            If wc is not equal to 32:
                If wc is not equal to 9:
                    Set ws_skip to ws_skip + doc_len
                End If
            End If
            Set ws_skip to ws_skip + 1
        End While
        If ws_skip > doc_len:
            Set ws_skip to ws_skip - doc_len
        End If

        Note: Check for "End Type" (E=69, n=110, d=100)
        Let end_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ws_skip
        If end_ch is equal to 69:
            If ws_skip + 2 < doc_len:
                Let end_n be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ws_skip + 1
                Let end_d be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, ws_skip + 2
                If end_n is equal to 110:
                    If end_d is equal to 100:
                        Note: Found "End" - stop parsing fields
                        Set field_scan to doc_len
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        If field_scan < doc_len:
            Note: Extract field name (from ws_skip to next space or " as ")
            Let fname_start be ws_skip
            Let fname_end be fname_start
            While fname_end < doc_len:
                Let fc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, fname_end
                If fc is equal to 32:
                    Set fname_end to fname_end + doc_len
                Otherwise If fc is equal to 10:
                    Set fname_end to fname_end + doc_len
                Otherwise:
                    Set fname_end to fname_end + 1
                End If
            End While
            If fname_end > doc_len:
                Set fname_end to fname_end - doc_len
            End If

            Let fname_len be fname_end - fname_start
            If fname_len > 0:
                If fname_len < 128:
                    Let field_name be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with fname_len + 1
                    If field_name is not equal to 0:
                        Let fi be 0
                        While fi < fname_len:
                            Let fb be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, fname_start + fi
                            Let dummy_fc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with field_name, fi, fb
                            Set fi to fi + 1
                        End While
                        Let dummy_ft be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with field_name, fname_len, 0

                        Note: Create completion item for this field
                        Let item be proc create_completion_item with field_name, COMPLETION_KIND_FIELD, 0, field_name, 0
                        If item is not equal to 0:
                            Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8
                            Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 16
                            If current_size < capacity:
                                Let items_data be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 0
                                Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with items_data, current_size multiplied by 8, item
                                Let dummy_inc be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_list, 8, current_size + 1
                                Set fields_added to fields_added + 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Note: Advance to next line
            Let nl_scan be fname_end
            While nl_scan < doc_len:
                Let nlc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with document_text, nl_scan
                If nlc is equal to 10:
                    Set field_scan to nl_scan + 1
                    Set nl_scan to doc_len
                Otherwise:
                    Set nl_scan to nl_scan + 1
                End If
            End While
            If nl_scan is equal to doc_len:
                Set field_scan to doc_len
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return fields_added
End Process
